OL,7,FIt also called on employers to return
OL,8,Fto the negotiating table with a
OL,9,F"significantly improved" offer,
OL,10,Fwarning of "widespread disruption" if
OL,11,Findustrial action were to take place.
OL,13,FGarry Ross, EIS ULA national officer,
OL,14,Fsaid: "This 1.4% offer is not just
OL,15,Fdisappointing, it is derisory and does
OL,16,Fnot reflect the dedication and
OL,17,Fexpertise of our university lecturers
OL,18,Fand academic-related members.
