OL,7,FA Scottish Government spokesperson
OL,8,Fsaid: "Staffing and operational
OL,9,Fmatters are the responsibility of
OL,10,Findividual universities.
OL,12,F"The Scottish Government is not
OL,13,Fdirectly involved in higher education
OL,14,Fpay negotiations, but we are
OL,15,Fabsolutely clear that Fair Work must
OL,16,Fbe the guiding principle for all
OL,17,Femployment-related decisions, and we
OL,18,Fcontinue to urge university management
OL,19,Fand the respective trade unions to
OL,20,Freach decisions that ensure employees
OL,21,Fare treated fairly."
